Prohibited or Restricted Items on WhatNew

WhatNew Support June 24, 2025 at 6:28 AM

{/* ===== Prohibited & Restricted Items Policy Section ===== */}

While we encourage WhatNew sellers to offer a diversity of items on the platform, there are some items that WhatNew does not support at this time, or that require additional restrictions to sell on WhatNew.

Our decision to prohibit or restrict certain items is based on varied reasons – some items pose legal or safety risks to the WhatNew community, some negatively impact user experience, and others aren’t well-suited for the platform at this time.

Sellers must ensure all items comply with applicable laws in their jurisdiction and that of their buyers. They must also meet all shipping terms and requirements in their region (e.g., USPS rules in the U.S.).

Adult & Explicit Items

WhatNew does not permit the sale of sex toys or sexually explicit items. Review our Adult & Explicit Items Policy for full details on acceptable content and when to use the Explicit Content toggle.

Alcohol

Alcohol products — including spirits, wine, and beer — cannot be sold or given away on WhatNew.

Air Guns, Pellet Guns, BB Guns, and Toy Guns

  • Permitted only within the U.S. in the Knives & Hunting category.
  • Airsoft guns must have a blaze orange tip (¼ inch or longer).
  • Caliber must be 0.25 or smaller.
  • All sales must comply with applicable laws.
  • Toy guns must be clearly marked as toys and not resemble real firearms.
  • Caps for toy guns are prohibited under WhatNew’s Hazardous Materials Policy.

Animal-Related Policy

WhatNew has specific rules around the sale of animals and animal products. Refer to our Animal Product Policy for details.

Bombs, Explosives, and Fireworks

These are strictly prohibited, including bombs, fireworks, sparklers, and related components or instructions.

Cannabis, CBD, and Hemp Items

WhatNew does not permit cannabis, THC, or CBD items. Only hemp-based products are currently allowed.

Cosmetics

See WhatNew’s Cosmetics Policy for rules on selling beauty and skincare products.

Credit & Debit Cards

The sale or giveaway of credit cards, debit cards, or cash is not permitted. Collectible currency is allowed under Coins and Money.

Embargoed Items

Items from or connected to embargoed regions (e.g., Cuba, Iran, North Korea, Syria, Crimea) are prohibited.

Expired Items

Expired items generally cannot be sold unless disclosed and clearly offered as collectibles.

Falsified Documents & Illegal Activity

Items promoting illegal or deceptive activity (e.g., fake IDs, hacking tools, or falsified documents) are not allowed.

Firearms, Ammunition, and Accessories

Refer to WhatNew’s Firearms & Firearm Parts Policy for permitted items and rules.

Food & Drink

Check WhatNew’s Food & Drink Policy for details on permitted consumables.

Gambling Products

Gambling-related items (e.g., lottery or raffle tickets, slot machines) are prohibited.

Hateful & Derogatory Items

Items that promote hate, violence, or discrimination based on protected characteristics are strictly banned.

Hazardous Materials & Flammable Substances

Hazardous, flammable, or toxic materials are not allowed. See the Hazardous Materials Policy for full details.

Human Parts & Remains

Human remains, bones, and fluids are not permitted for sale or giveaway on WhatNew.

Illegal or Harmful Content

Items that depict or promote illegal activity, graphic violence, or exploitation are strictly forbidden.

Drugs & Paraphernalia

Illegal drugs, drug-related items, and paraphernalia are prohibited on the platform.

Counterfeit & IP-Infringing Items

WhatNew prohibits the sale of counterfeit goods. Review our Counterfeit and IP Policy for more details.

Knives

Knives and related items must comply with WhatNew’s Knives Policy and applicable local laws.

Medical & Health Items

Prescription medicines and devices are not allowed. Unopened vitamins or supplements may be sold if compliant.

Personal Information

The sale or sharing of others’ personal information is prohibited.

Plants

See WhatNew’s Plant Policy and related best practices for selling plants and seeds.

Recalled Products

Recalled items cannot be listed or sold.

Financial Instruments

Stocks, securities, and related assets cannot be sold. Gift cards are permitted.

Stolen Items

Stolen goods are not permitted.

Tobacco & E-Cigarettes

Tobacco and nicotine products are not allowed. Empty collectible cigarette packs and tobacco pipes are exceptions.

Unknown Items

Sellers cannot list unknown or unclaimed items for sale.

Violent Items

Items that glorify, promote, or depict violence or self-harm are strictly prohibited.

Weapons & Self-Defense

Harmful weapons are not allowed. Permitted items include handcuffs, slingshots, crossbows, and foam training weapons.
